{"id": "u021", "student_turn": "I get really energized when there's a lively debate. Pushing back on ideas is how I think.", "expected": {"personality": [{"facet": "conflict_style", "value": "thrives in debate", "evidence": "I get really energized when there's a lively debate"}], "confidence": {"personality": 0.9}}, "notes": "Conflict style with concrete evidence — high confidence."}
{"id": "u022", "student_turn": "Big lecture halls drain me. After 90 students I just shut down.", "expected": {"personality": [{"facet": "peer_style", "value": "small cohort preference", "evidence": "Big lecture halls drain me"}], "confidence": {"personality": 0.85}}, "notes": "Negative framing — extract the affirmative preference (small cohort)."}
{"id": "u023", "student_turn": "I want to live somewhere with real seasons. Florida would crush me.", "expected": {"personality": [{"facet": "location_emotional", "value": "real seasons / non-tropical", "evidence": "I want to live somewhere with real seasons"}], "confidence": {"personality": 0.85}}, "notes": "Location_emotional, not basic.location_prefs (this is about feel, not specific places)."}
{"id": "u024", "student_turn": "I think most institutions get safety wrong by treating it as a checkbox. Real safety is the texture of how people treat each other.", "expected": {"identity": [{"facet": "view", "claim": "safety is interpersonal texture, not institutional checkboxes", "evidence": "Real safety is the texture of how people treat each other"}], "confidence": {"identity": 0.9}}, "notes": "Worldview claim — defended position with explanation. High-quality identity signal."}
{"id": "u025", "student_turn": "I used to think I wanted a research career, but I noticed I avoid the lab on weekends. Maybe I just liked the idea.", "expected": {"identity": [{"facet": "self_awareness", "claim": "noticed weekend avoidance contradicts stated research aspiration", "evidence": "I noticed I avoid the lab on weekends. Maybe I just liked the idea"}], "confidence": {"identity": 0.9}}, "notes": "Premium self-awareness — observed pattern + revised conclusion."}
{"id": "u026", "student_turn": "Honestly the deepest thing I value is loyalty. I'd take a worse program with people I trust over a great program with strangers.", "expected": {"identity": [{"facet": "value", "claim": "loyalty over institutional prestige", "evidence": "I'd take a worse program with people I trust over a great program with strangers"}], "confidence": {"identity": 0.9}}, "notes": "Strong value claim with the tradeoff explicitly named — ideal identity material."}
{"id": "u027", "student_turn": "I keep saying community matters most to me but I haven't actually built one. Maybe I value it more in theory than in practice.", "expected": {"identity": [{"facet": "self_awareness", "claim": "noticed gap between professed value of community and actual community-building behavior", "evidence": "I haven't actually built one. Maybe I value it more in theory than in practice"}], "confidence": {"identity": 0.9}}, "notes": "Self-awareness with concrete evidence of behavior contradicting belief."}
