{"id": "u029", "student_turn": "I love teaching kids math. Watching the moment something clicks for someone — that's the thing.", "expected": {"personality": [{"facet": "passion", "value": "teaching / mentorship", "evidence": "Watching the moment something clicks for someone — that's the thing"}], "confidence": {"personality": 0.9}}, "notes": "Passion with vivid concrete evidence."}
{"id": "u030", "student_turn": "I think colleges are obsessed with potential and ignore who someone actually is right now.", "expected": {"identity": [{"facet": "view", "claim": "colleges over-emphasize potential at the expense of present-self recognition", "evidence": "colleges are obsessed with potential and ignore who someone actually is right now"}], "confidence": {"identity": 0.85}}, "notes": "View, not value — meta-commentary on how-things-work."}
{"id": "u031", "student_turn": "When someone disagrees with me hard I usually get quiet and reconsider. I don't fight on the spot.", "expected": {"personality": [{"facet": "conflict_style", "value": "absorbs and reconsiders", "evidence": "I usually get quiet and reconsider. I don't fight on the spot"}], "confidence": {"personality": 0.85}}, "notes": "Conflict style — opposite of debate-thriving. Both are valid; extract with evidence."}
{"id": "u032", "student_turn": "I've been told I'm intense. I think I just care more than is socially convenient.", "expected": {"identity": [{"facet": "self_awareness", "claim": "self-described as intense; reframed as care exceeding social norms", "evidence": "I've been told I'm intense. I think I just care more than is socially convenient"}], "confidence": {"identity": 0.85}}, "notes": "External feedback + self-reframe = self-awareness."}
{"id": "u033", "student_turn": "I really like math.", "expected": {"personality": [{"facet": "interest", "value": "math", "evidence": "I really like math"}], "confidence": {"personality": 0.55}}, "notes": "Generic statement; interest at modest confidence — NOT a passion or identity claim."}
{"id": "u034", "student_turn": "What gets me out of bed isn't grades. It's the satisfaction of making something work that didn't before.", "expected": {"identity": [{"facet": "value", "claim": "intrinsic motivation from making things work over external validation", "evidence": "What gets me out of bed isn't grades. It's the satisfaction of making something work"}], "confidence": {"identity": 0.85}}, "notes": "Value claim contrasting intrinsic vs extrinsic — strong identity material."}
{"id": "u035", "student_turn": "I work best alone. Group projects historically drained me — I end up doing the work plus managing everyone else's pace.", "expected": {"personality": [{"facet": "peer_style", "value": "independent / introvert-leaning", "evidence": "I work best alone"}, {"facet": "connection_style", "value": "task-driven over collaborative", "evidence": "Group projects historically drained me"}], "confidence": {"personality": 0.85}}, "notes": "Multi-signal turn — peer_style AND connection_style both extracted with separate evidence."}
{"id": "u036", "student_turn": "City energy makes me feel alive. I'd shrivel in a small town.", "expected": {"personality": [{"facet": "location_emotional", "value": "urban energy", "evidence": "City energy makes me feel alive"}], "confidence": {"personality": 0.9}}, "notes": "Location_emotional facet — the *feel* preference."}
{"id": "u037", "student_turn": "I want to be the person my younger sister could call when she gets stuck on something.", "expected": {"identity": [{"facet": "value", "claim": "wants to be a reliable resource for family", "evidence": "the person my younger sister could call when she gets stuck on something"}], "confidence": {"identity": 0.85}}, "notes": "Value claim with concrete behavioral grounding."}
{"id": "u038", "student_turn": "Sometimes I worry I picked CS because my dad is in CS. I don't actually know if I'd love it without that nudge.", "expected": {"identity": [{"facet": "self_awareness", "claim": "uncertainty about whether CS choice is autonomous vs paternal influence", "evidence": "I worry I picked CS because my dad is in CS"}], "confidence": {"identity": 0.9}}, "notes": "Self-awareness with attribution of cause + admitted uncertainty."}
{"id": "u039", "student_turn": "I'm into climbing, music, and reading philosophy on the train.", "expected": {"personality": [{"facet": "interest", "value": "climbing / music / philosophy", "evidence": "I'm into climbing, music, and reading philosophy on the train"}], "confidence": {"personality": 0.85}}, "notes": "Multiple interests; extract as one entry with combined value."}
{"id": "u040", "student_turn": "Work matters more than where you work. I think people obsess over rankings to compensate for not knowing what they want.", "expected": {"identity": [{"facet": "view", "claim": "rankings obsession is a symptom of self-knowledge deficit", "evidence": "people obsess over rankings to compensate for not knowing what they want"}], "confidence": {"identity": 0.9}}, "notes": "View claim with diagnostic / mechanism — strong worldview signal."}
{"id": "u041", "student_turn": "I think every student should be required to take a year off before college.", "expected": {"identity": [{"facet": "belief", "claim": "mandatory gap year would improve college readiness", "evidence": "every student should be required to take a year off before college"}], "confidence": {"identity": 0.85}}, "notes": "Prescriptive belief, not value — extract as facet=belief, not value."}
{"id": "u042", "student_turn": "I do my best work when someone I respect is watching. I'm honestly motivated by external validation, even though I know I shouldn't be.", "expected": {"identity": [{"facet": "self_awareness", "claim": "acknowledges external-validation motivation while normatively conflicted about it", "evidence": "I'm honestly motivated by external validation, even though I know I shouldn't be"}], "confidence": {"identity": 0.9}}, "notes": "High-grade self-awareness — admission + normative tension."}
